ed to Battle > VS Mode > press START/OPTIONS button (NOT PS button)
- Player 2 wait until Player 1 completes the above, then press START/OPTIONS button (NOT PS button)

In the event both Players controllers register as Player 1:
1) Player 1 > re-selects the MAIN User Profile from the quick menu, proceeds to Battle > VS Mode > press START/OPTIONS button (NOT PS button) then:
2) Player 2 > selects the GUEST User Profile from the quick menu (do NOT go to the Xbox Home Screen)","## SNK WORLD CHAMPIONSHIP QUALIFIER
- Winner will be invited to the SNK World Championship 2025

## ADDITIONAL RULES
- DRAW: In the event of a tied Match declared by a “Draw” or “Double K.O.” on the Game screen, the Match will not be scored and both Players will replay the tied Match with the same character and stage selections.

- MATCH DISRUPTIONS: In the event of a Player disruption caused by pausing or disconnecting a controller (intentionally or accidentally), the Player who caused the disruption will forfeit the current round of the Match. If a Match Disruption occurs that is out of control of the Players, such as a power failure or Bloom Glitch, the Tournament Organizer shall order to restart the Match.

- CONTROLLERS: It is each Players responsibility to know how to pair their controller with Xbox Series. Players are responsible for bringing a functional controller equipped with correct wire/cable (versus a charging only cable). Converters will be provided at Tournament Setups (Brook Wingman XB3/XB1/XB2 or Mayflash MagicX). If using a converter, plug in controller and wait 1-2 seconds before use.

## ADDITIONAL NOTES
- Casual setups for Free Play will be available (with converters) on Tournament Day and if there is sufficient space (and VG/FFXVII Staff allows), 1-2 casual setups may be available (with converters) for free play during pools. Any questions or concerns about converters or controllers, DM Ke11yAnn - I may have XB3, XB1, XB2, and MayFlash Magic X converters on hand for use at setups, please don't hesitate to ask.",,12:00pm,,True,,True,Likely,,rec3MGGScx1f0hNeK,"Converters will be provided to participants (Brook Wingman XB3 and XB1/XB2/MagicX will be available). 

Casual setups will be provided (some casual setups will include converters).

It is each players responsibility to know how to pair their controller with Xbox Series (if unsure, or want to verify, @ me before the Tournament starts). It is each Players responsibility to ensure they use a functional controller equipped with the correct cable (versus a charging only cable).

Any questions or concerns about converters or controllers, @ me. I'll have XB1, XB2, and MayFlash Magic X converters on hand as well.",120Hz+ displays are required (preferably MSI if possible),,"SNK WORLD CHAMPIONSHIP QUALIFIER
- Winner will be invited to the SNK World Championship 2025",,
